column5: So this ice season has been devoteted to breakining my 4 year loosing streak for the whitey.  Year 5 is going to be here soon . Ive gone deep/shallow hit drops stll cant find them??    roled a few over in the usual haunts...      Don.  ARRRRG.
Keep at it Saltyd.... I have a feeling you're going to hookup onto one... one of these days   Don't give up
I still have yet to get one as well so I feel your pain!!!!!
One whitey through the ice this year, lots and lots of lake trout however.
Put the gold spoon on again next year, next year you will savour your catch.
They say that two tone ice Wiliiams(gold/silver),works well.Stay at it I am  Not really lol./sometimes.
Simcoe white fish have been killing me this year too, as you already know...
I got one,,,,,,,,,,,,,,, Til the riv cleans up,it,s pike and crappie.   MMMMMMMMMM CRAPPIE.
I'll have to fly back next winter and show you and Salty how its done lol,  The good Lord knows I can't catch any up here  at least simcoe liked me
Last year,whities were crazy hook ups.More whities then lakers. It,s going to be interesting to see what the reports will be like come opener on the open water.
Keep at it Don, sometimes they just wont bite....even when dey is dere
I don't normally try for them on open water.  But team 1 needs a white fish.  So I might have a stab at them This spring.
